Fix a typo'd header guard in nasa/PSP's RTEMS coverage stub.

The opening #ifndef says OVERRIDE_TOOIMPL_H while the #define says
OVERRIDE_TODIMPL_H (TOO- vs TOD-). GCC's -Werror=header-guard catches the
mismatch, and cFS builds the PSP coverage targets during `make install` --
so `make native_std.install` fails outright on any reasonably recent GCC,
even though nothing Besom touches is involved:

  todimpl.h:20: error: header guard 'OVERRIDE_TOOIMPL_H' followed by
  '#define' of a different macro [-Werror=header-guard]

This is an upstream nasa/PSP bug, not a Besom one, and it is unrelated to
the simulated timebase. It is carried here only so the build instructions
in the README actually complete. Upstreaming it is the real fix.

diff --git a/unit-test-coverage/ut-stubs/override_inc/rtems/score/todimpl.h b/unit-test-coverage/ut-stubs/override_inc/rtems/score/todimpl.h
index 408b28c..632aa89 100644
--- a/unit-test-coverage/ut-stubs/override_inc/rtems/score/todimpl.h
+++ b/unit-test-coverage/ut-stubs/override_inc/rtems/score/todimpl.h
@@ -17,7 +17,7 @@
  ************************************************************************/
 
 /* PSP coverage stub replacement for todimpl.h */
-#ifndef OVERRIDE_TOOIMPL_H
+#ifndef OVERRIDE_TODIMPL_H
 #define OVERRIDE_TODIMPL_H
 
 #include "PCS_todimpl.h"
